<omgroup xml:id="introduction">
 <metadata><dc:title>Introduction</dc:title></metadata>
 <omtext xml:id="intro.1">
  <CMP>
   This theory collection makes available an interdependent collection of theories
   that define logics. These logics are a foundation for the interoperability and
   communication between reasoning services on <phrase
   style="acronym">MathWeb</phrase>.
  </CMP>
 </omtext>
</omgroup>


<omgroup xml:id="prop-log">
 <metadata><dc:title>Propositional Logics</dc:title></metadata>
 <omtext xml:id="prop-log-intro">
  <CMP>
   Propositional logics are logics that abstract from the inner structure of
   statements, and only study their interrelation in complex formulae built up
   from propositional connectives.
  </CMP>
 </omtext>
 <ref type="include" xref="truthtables.omdoc#truthtables"/>
